-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-14T15:57:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/russian-equities-gazprom-neft-sistema-veropharm-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  advanced
0.5 percent to 1,504.92 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow,
erasing an earlier loss of as much as 1 percent. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index fell 0.1 percent to 1,570.38.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX), the oil-producing unit of
Russiaâ€™s gas export monopoly, fell for the second day, losing
0.5 percent to 125.77 rubles. Crude for October delivery
declined $2 to $88.21 a barrel in  New York  on concern the
European debt crisis will temper fuel demand.  AFK Sistema (AFKC RX) rose to its highest level in four
weeks, adding 2.5 percent to 26.55 rubles after more than
doubling second-quarter profit from a year earlier on increased
earnings at its oil unit.  OAO Veropharm (VFRM RX) climbed for the second day,
increasing 1.7 percent to 961.9 rubles after the Russian
pharmaceuticals company said profit for the first half of this
year jumped 21 percent to 881 million rubles ($29 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
